Russian Dance Company Gives Premiere 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Samjiyon, June 18 (KCNA) -- The State Academic Moiseyev Dance Company of Russia on a visit to the DPRK gave its premiere at the Samjiyon County House of Culture in Ryanggang Province on June 18. 
 The dance company, widely known to the army and people of Korea through its performances in Pyongyang and local cities during its Korea visits, has come here with folk dance works of Russia and different countries it sincerely prepared. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the audience were Kim Kyong Ho, chief secretary of the Ryanggang Provincial Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, and Ri Kong Phil, chairman of the Ryanggang Provincial People's Committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The dance company put colorful numbers on the stage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Dance works "Guerrillas" and "Summer", typical works of the company, were acclaimed by the audience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Performers demonstrated the face of influential and authoritative dance company in folk dances of different countries and nations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance left deep impressions to the audience as it vividly showed the emotion and life feelings of the Russian people and different nations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was warmly acclaimed by the audience for its rich and colorful contents and high artistic representation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A floral basket was given to the performers for their successful performance.
 The company's performance continues.

Special Envoy of DPRK Government Speaks at South Summit 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 19 (KCNA) -- The government and people of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea will fulfill their responsibility and duty to expand and develop south-south cooperation so as to contribute to building a peaceful, prosperous and independent world.
 Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs Choe Su Hon, who is a special envoy of the DPRK government, said this in a speech at the 2nd South Summit held in Qatar on June 15 and 16. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed the conviction that the summit would be a historic occasion of demonstrating once again the political will and united might of South countries to establish a fair international economic order and strengthen south-south cooperation.
 Stating that unilateralism based on the idea of "strength almighty" is violating the rules and order of international relations and posing a serious threat to economic development of South countries, he went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK delegation considers that the summit should pay a special attention to the following issues in adopting the strategy of development and action program of the South to cope with the present challenges: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 First, the current summit should be an opportunity to commit itself once again to the firm political will of the South countries to cope with the present international challenges with their concerted efforts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Second, the summit should be an occasion of further developing  south-south cooperation based on collective self-reliance and give great vigor to establishing new economic relations among the South countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Third, the summit should be an occasion of taking practical measures for joint action to provide favorable international circumstances and conditions for the economic growth and development of those countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The constant socio-political stability in the DPRK serves as a basic motive force and a firm guarantee for the sustained development of economy and dynamic development of south-south cooperation between developing countries, he noted, and stressed: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has consistently maintained the idea on south-south cooperation created by President Kim Il Sung as one of fundamental guidelines of its foreign policy line and made a possible contribution to materializing the joint strategy and joint action of the South countries.

Presentation of Articles Written by Foreign Students Here 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 19 (KCNA) -- "Song of Praising Great Man," a meeting for presenting articles written by foreign students studying at Kim Il Sung University was held at the Taedonggang Club for the Diplomatic Corps on June 18 on the occasion of leader Kim Jong Il's start of work at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 At the meeting which began with chorus "Song of General   Kim Jong Il" students presented their works carrying their ardent reverence for President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In occasional notes "Before an immortal monument to his autographs", poem "Song of the eternal sun" and other works performers expressed deep reverence of humankind for the President and Kim Jong Il who is carrying forward his cause. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In poem "Song sung on Ryonggun Peak" and record of impression "A country of Songun politics", Chinese and Iranian students stressed that as led by Kim Jong Il the DPRK is throwing bright rays all over the world as a great country shining with Songun politics.
 Diary "Along the trace of the great man" and written impressions "My pride" expressed eulogy for Kim Jong Il. Korean songs including immortal masterpiece "Azalea" and "My Blessed Life" were sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting ended with chorus of the Korean song "Dear Name".

Japanese Chief Executive's Seoul Visit Rejected 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 19 (KCNA) -- Political parties and civic and public organizations in south Korea reportedly held press conferences one after another in front of the Japanese embassy in Seoul on June 17, protesting against the Japanese chief executive's projected trip to Seoul.
 The Democratic Workers' Party charged that the chief executive's visit to south Korea is planned at a time when Japan has become all the more undisguised in its moves to revive militarism as evidenced by its distortion of history, its claim to Tok Islet, its bid for a permanent membership of the UN Security Council, its call for sanctions against the north and the racket kicked up by it over "human rights in north Korea." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that peace on the Korean Peninsula and in other parts of Northeast Asia has been seriously threatened by Japan, the Democratic Workers' Party stated that it can not repress concern over the revision of the "Pacifist Constitution" and the intensified military alliance between the U.S. and Japan aimed to emerge a military giant. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Members of civic and public organizations under the National People's Solidarity and the Reunification Solidarity underlined the need to clearly understand that lurking behind the Japanese chief executive's Seoul trip is his intention to intensify the U.S.-Japan security system and the south Korea-U.S.-Japan alliance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They stated that the Seoul trip of the Japanese chief executive playing the role of a proxy of the U.S. is an act of threatening peace in the Korean Peninsula and other parts of Northeast Asia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They said they would hold a "joint meeting of civic and public organizations involving civic, reunification and mass movement camps to check Japan's revival of militarism and its bid for a permanent seat of the UN Security Council". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants held a ceremony of trampling underfoot a gourd dipper bearing letters "plunder of dominium over Tok Islet", "revival of militarism", "bid for permanent membership of UN Security Council" and "distortion of history".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the same day members of the Kochang Branch of the Society of Bereaved Families of Pacific War Victims demanded a direct apology and compensation of Japan for its past crimes and went on strike against the Seoul visit of the Japanese chief executive.

Minju Joson on Achievements of June 15 Grand Festival for Reunification 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 19 (KCNA) -- The nation's movement for reunification has been put on a higher stage by the June 15 grand festival for national reunification which gave confidence and courage to the 70 million fellow countrymen in their efforts to thoroughly implement the North-South Joint Declaration and dealt a telling blow to the foreign aggressors who are working hard to split and alienate the Korean nation. Minju Joson says this in a signed commentary today.
 The Korean nation is faced with an important task to consolidate the achievements of the June 15 grand festival, the commentary says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to fulfill the task the "declaration of national reunification" adopted at the meeting for national reunification marking the 5th anniversary of the publication of the June 15 joint declaration should be carried through. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The interests common to the nation should be placed first, joint steps promoted, solidarity strengthened and multi-lateral cooperation intensified between authorities and between non-governmental organizations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The struggle for peace against war should be further strengthened to remove the danger of nuclear war and build up a ground for a peaceable life with the concerted efforts of the whole nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The June 15 Joint Committee that sponsored the grand festival is the parent body of great national unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The commentary calls for developing the joint committee into the most extensive and powerful organization for the patriotic movement for reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 70 million fellow countrymen should open a new phase of national reunification by stepping up the great march of the nation for independence, peace and reunification this year marking the fifth anniversary of the publication of the June 15 joint declaration, conscious of being the masters who open a new era of national reunification, it concludes.

S. Korea Visit of Japanese Chief Executive Protested 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 19 (KCNA) -- An all-people rally against Koizumi's tour to south Korea was reportedly held at the Thapgol Park in Seoul on June 17 under the sponsorship of the Headquarters of the Student Movement for Defending Tok Islet, checking the distortion of history and liquidating the remnants of pro-Japanese elements.
 Ri Ju Hui, chairperson of the Student Committee of the south Korean Democratic Workers' Party, addressing the rally, said that what the people concern most is to make Japan reflect on its past history, stop distorting history and withdraw its claim to Tok Islet. Questioning if "talks" with no such preconditions are needed, Ri said that they cannot allow the "talks" to bind south Korea in the frame of military alliance with the U.S. and Japan and force it to join in the front of confrontation with the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jin Man, chairman of the General Student Council of Chungang University, said that it is clear that the forthcoming "talks" are for preparing a war and strengthening war alliance. He accused Japan of playing the role of a proxy of the U.S. in realizing its strategy of domination over Northeast Asia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jo Jong Won, head of the action team of the headquarters, referred to information activities conducted among Seoul citizens from June 6 and stressed that Japanese chief executive's tour to south Korea would be certainly checked. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After the rally, participants marched up to the Japanese embassy in Seoul, shouting slogans such as "We oppose Koizumi's south Korea visit".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They tried to convey a letter of protest to the Japanese embassy, but police blocked them.

Anniversary of June 15 Joint Declaration Observed in Kyrgyzstan 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 18 (KCNA) -- The United Confederation of Koreans in Kyrgyzstan held a meeting and photo exhibition on June 15 to mark the fifth anniversary of the publication of the historic June 15 North-South Joint Declaration.
 Pak Kyong Ho, chairman of the confederation, addressing the meeting, noted that as there is the joint declaration published thanks to the matchless pluck and patriotic idea of leader Kim Jong Il the reunification of the nation and the country is certain to be achieved on the basis of the idea "By our nation itself." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Overseas Koreans will join the compatriots in the homeland in their more vigorous struggle to implement the joint declaration, he stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then the floor was taken by representatives of compatriots. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants looked round a photo exhibition on the theme of "Great footprints left on the long journey for the Songun leadership."

Bulletins Issued in Peru and Czech Republic
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 18 (KCNA) -- An information bulletin titled "Leader Kim Jong Il and the Workers' Party of Korea" was published by the Peru Group for the Study of Kimilsungism on June 10 on the occasion of the 41st anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's start of work at the WPK Central Committee and the 5th anniversary of the publication of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration.
 The bulletin noted that Kim Jong Il has developed the WPK into the Party of President Kim Il Sung which takes the Juche idea as its only guiding idea, a militant organization firmly based on the monolithic leadership system of the leader and a political organization that upholds and strengthens the unity and cohesion of the whole society.
 Thanks to the Songun politics pursued by Kim Jong Il, socialist Korea has become a steel-like entity as the servicepersons and people are united around its headquarters and share the same idea and fighting trait. The reunification of Korea is sure to be achieved as there is the Songun politics which guarantees the implementation of the joint declaration, it stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An information bulletin titled "On the occasion of the fifth anniversary of the publication of the North-South Joint Declaration" was published at a county committee of the Communist Party of Bohemia and Moravia on June 8. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bulletin in an article said that the joint declaration adopted in June of 2000 called for achieving the country's reunification on the basis of the three principles--independence, peaceful reunification and great national unity--by the concerted efforts of the Koreans, recalling that since the publication of the joint declaration grand festivals for national reunification have been held in the north and the south of Korea and exchange and cooperation made in various fields including politics, economy, culture and sports. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The joint declaration serves as an important milestone for Korea's reunification, it added.

Japanese Minister Denounced for His Reckless Remarks
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 18 (KCNA) -- Nakayama, Japanese minister of Education and Science, recently asserted that it is necessary to teach students that Tok Islet is part of the territory of Japan, while negating the sexual slavery committed by Japan in the past.
 In this regard Rodong Sinmun in a signed commentary says: What Nakayama uttered is touching off bitter resentment among the Koreans as it is an unpardonable insult to and mockery of the Korean nation which had suffered all sorts of pain under the occupation of the Japanese imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reckless remarks made by the educational chief of Japan negating the past aggression and bestial crimes of Japan and agitating the operation to seize Tok Islet are unthinkable apart from the moves for militarization that have become evermore undisguised in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His assertion that it is necessary to teach students that Tok Islet is part of the territory of Japan and there was no sexual slavery for the imperial Japanese army is nothing but a trick to infuse a militarist view on history into the present and coming generations of Japan in a bid to drive them to overseas expansion and reinvasion of Korea. This precisely reflects the criminal intention and policy of the Japanese militarists. Nakayama's remarks represent the policy of the Japanese government. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No attempt to distort or cover up history can ever change or write it off. The Japanese reactionaries' distortion of history and moves to grab Tok Islet are as foolish an act as throwing Japan into an abyss of ruin.

GIs' Murder of S. Korean Woman Assailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 18 (KCNA) -- A south Korean woman was killed by a U.S. army truck at a road intersection in Tongduchon, south Korea, a few days before the third anniversary of the murder of two schoolgirls by a U.S. armored car.
 The truth about the case has been brought to light. According to it, a representative of the Democratic Workers' Party and members of civic organizations in charge of the case conducted an investigation into the case. In the course of investigating the case, keeping in touch with the relevant police station, they have found out the fact that a GI on the truck saw that woman before the incident took place and its driver, too, felt something wrong before stopping the truck. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is quite different to the statements made by the two GI assailants at the outset of the investigation that they did not see any woman nor their truck hit her. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Commenting on it, a Minju Joson news analyst today brands the case as a thrice-cursed brutal murder deliberately committed by the GIs present in south Korea.
 The news analyst further says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This case clearly proves once again that the U.S. imperialists are a group of murderers regarding human-killing as their job and pleasure with whom the Korean nation can never live under the same sky. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists have kept south Korea under their occupation for more than half a century, inflicting all sorts of misfortune and sufferings upon the south Korean people. Not content with it, they are now seeking to bring a nuclear war disaster to the entire Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reality proves that without getting the U.S. forces withdrawn from south Korea, is it impossible for the south Korean people to be free from misfortune and sufferings and for the Korean nation to avoid such nuclear war disaster. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the Koreans should turn out as one in the courageous anti-U.S. struggle to drive the U.S. imperialist aggression forces, a group of blood-thirsty man-killers, out of south Korea at an early date.

Anniversary of Publication of Joint Declaration Commemorated in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 18 (KCNA) -- Functions took place in different parts of south Korea on the occasion of the 5th anniversary of the publication of the June 15 joint declaration, according to a news report.
 A special exhibition was held in Pusan on June 15 under the sponsorship of the Pusan Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display at the exhibition in the plaza of Pusan Railway Station were materials showing the significance of the joint declaration and the proud course of five years after its publication and materials disclosing the U.S. threat of war and economic subjugation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was said that a large number of citizens in Pusan who visited the venue of the exhibition were replete with will to reunify the country with the concerted efforts of the Korean nation itself. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the Chonan Headquarters for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration held a 6.15 km running contest of citizens for reunification in the plaza of the Chonan all-round playground on June 12. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At least 500 citizens from all walks of life participated in the contest. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The contest was followed by an art performance.

Probe into GI Murder of S. Korean Woman Urged
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 18 (KCNA) -- The Youth and Students Solidarity for Implementing the June 15 South-North Joint Declaration reportedly issued a statement on June 12, demanding a thorough probe into the U.S. soldiers' murder of a south Korean woman by a truck and punishment of criminals.
 The recent case was not just an accident but evidently a deliberate murder, the statement said, adding: What infuriates us is that the U.S. military side had procrastinated an inspection of the scene, talking about concern over possible "infringement upon the mourning right" and threat of "personal safety" afraid of the revelation of its soldiers' deliberate action, before conducting a surprise investigation by itself two days after the incident. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement urged the south Koreans not to be taken in any longer by the U.S. forces' operation to cover up the murder case, ensure thorough investigation and probe the truth behind the case so as to prevent the recurrence of such tragedy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It called for making this year, 60 years after the U.S. military occupation of south Korea and three years after the death of Hyo Sun and Mi Son, as a nationwide struggle for the withdrawal of the U.S. troops.

Art Performance of Agricultural Workers Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Onchon , June 17 (KCNA) -- An art performance was given by the Art Squad of the Central Committee of the Union of Agricultural Workers of Korea at the Mayong Co-op Farm in Onchon County, South Phyongan Province on June 17 on the occasion of the 41st anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's start of work at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 It began with an ode and song "Song Devoted to Comrade Kim Jong Il". Put on the stage were colorful numbers such as male vocal solo and Pangchang "Korea, I Will Glorify Thee", an immortal famous work of Kim Jong Il, dialogic poem "Great Proclamation" and male chorus "Long Live the Workers' Party of Korea".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Male vocal solo and singing to the accompaniment of Oungum "The Blue Sky over My Country", mixed quintet of serial songs "Golden Ears of Rice Sway on Either Side of the Road Leading to the Frontline", a female vocal solo "Three Thousand-Ri of Taehongdan" and other numbers impressively deal with the resolution of the unionists and agricultural workers to bring a rich harvest to the land which has been defended and cultivated by Kim Jong Il while making ceaseless long journeys for Songun leadership.
 It was closed with a poem and chorus "We Will Hold Our General in Higher Esteem" and song "We Will Defend the Headquarters of the Revolution with Our Lives".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the audience were Kang Chang Uk, chairman of the UAWK Central Committee, Cha Pyong Yun, secretary of the South Phyongan Provincial Committee of the WPK, officials concerned and others.

U.S. Moves to Reorganize Its Forces Assailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 18 (KCNA) -- The U.S. moves to reorganize its forces present in south Korea is recently reaching a reckless stage, according to south Korean CBS and KBS. 
 The U.S. forces stationed in south Korea established a new multi-purpose air brigade in the 2nd Division of the U.S. army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An inaugural ceremony of the brigade took place in the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek, Kyonggi Province on June 16 with the attendance of the commander of the U.S. forces in south Korea and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 The brigade consists of two battalions which carry on the duty of offensive and reconnaissance by helicopters and a battalion of UH-60 helicopters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the 2nd Division was reorganized as a "future-oriented division" capable of carrying out even long distance operations on June 14.  It was announced on the same day that the existing 1st Brigade of the 2nd Division has been reorganized as the first heavily armed and mechanized combat brigade of the "rapid task force" with "strategic flexibility". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As already reported, the U.S. had rapidly stepped up its moves to strengthen the war capability of the 2nd Division, the main force for invasion of the north, in a bid to reorganize its forces in south Korea as a "rapid task force" which has high mobility and precision strike capacity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S announced it would complete the reorganization of the 2nd Division till this summer. It reorganized the 1st brigade under the division  as a "super brigade"  two or three times stronger than the strength of  the existing brigade armed with such up-to-date weapons as Striker armored cars and then again established new units, putting spurs on the final completion of reorganization. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The dangerous U.S. moves for reorganizing the armed forces is a grave provocation aimed to trample upon the desire of Koreans for national reunification which was gaining momentum during the June 15 grand festival for national reunification, and it is a revelation of its wild ambition to unleash a war of aggression, a nuclear war, on the Korean Peninsula at any cost.
